        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 10 at 3:28PM CDT until July 10 at 4:30PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>SVRLOT

The National Weather Service in Chicago has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Lee County in north central Illinois...

* Until 430 PM CDT.

* At 327 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Sterling,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Nelson, Nachusa, Eldena, Dixon, and Woodland Shores.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
